reviews.review: This wasn't a Star Wars movie and neither was it a Disney Star Wars movie. It wasn't even in between, it was just out there somewhere, trying to find itself. The writing decisions and plot was atrocious, definitely one of the worst movies to come out this year. This was an absolute disaster that made everything that happened in every one of the previous movie become meaningless. It's so ridiculous how it completely destroys every single thing that has happened in the series, an utter disaster that blows both new and old fans away. This movie should be more than enough proof of how bad Kathleen Kennedy has been for the franchise, if somehow her comments on the lack of source material did not show you that already.
A great visual show but a movie mess. Today we can give up the biggest saga of cinema.
The worst one yet! They wrapped it in a way which has made the ending of HBO's Game of thrones look good. And we all know how bad the last episode of GoT was.

I like star wars! I even enjoyed the last jedi, despite its problems. but this was just... so bad. the pacing. the dialogue.  the complete reversal of everything that happened in TLJ. the reversal of every pivotal plot point in this movie immediately after it happens.

I have been waiting so long for this epic conclusion and frankly, I appreciated this movie. It has good action, fun new characters and some good nostalgic call backs to the original trilogy. But when leaving the cinema, I was left with a ton of unanswered questions and few plot points that should have needed explanation. I also found it slow-paced at some times and we kind of drifted away from the main objective at some locations...
Overall it is a satisfying conclusion to the epic skywalker saga but sadly, not as good as I would have expected.

I had low expectations and was ready to forgive a lot of cringy, cheesy and illogical moments just for the sake of the franchise. But damn this was terrible.
It's like they started with an underwhelming plot, but then the editors took over and made every good moment there was in it fail to deliver the intended emotion. Instead of telling the story they focused on the main characters repeating the same vague sayings about faith and friendship over and over. 
I wish this never existed, so that we could get a different ending to the saga.
It really does wrap up the "saga" and brings the sequel trilogy to a satisfying conclusion

Amazing visuals as usual As well as the appearance of mythic characters. Too bad it gets ruined by a rushed story that tries to fix the errors of the previous episode and by plot devices that destroy the coherence of the fictional universe itself.
Leaps and bounds better then the last Jedi disaster. I'm glad it fixed some of that, it was fun... Not perfect but it was worth the ticket price.

There should be a judicial court that sentences people and organisations who commit crime to human culture. This movie not only stole time I could have used wasting on YouTube or a random streaming service to rewatch something for the tenth time, it also gave the last blow to my great memory of the original Star Wars movies (pre-Disney). Would prefer to be blissfully ignorant of this tragicomical plot line, but unfortunately it's too late. Don't watch it.
